%% Modified by Codex on 2026-03-16.
%% Scope: Root-agent routing plus the intake fields that must exist before slot search starts.

sequenceDiagram
  autonumber

  participant User as User
  participant RootAgent as voice_banking_agent
  participant AppointmentAgent as advisory_appointment_agent

  User->>RootAgent: "I want to book an appointment for mortgage advice"
  Note over RootAgent: Route to advisory_appointment_agent only when the utterance implies booking,<br/>rescheduling, cancellation, or explicit appointment management.<br/>Generic branch or ATM lookup stays in location_services_agent.

  alt generic location query only
    RootAgent->>RootAgent: Keep request in location_services_agent
    RootAgent-->>User: Continue branch or ATM discovery outside the appointment flow
  else booking or lifecycle semantics detected
    RootAgent->>AppointmentAgent: Route appointment journey

    alt new appointment
      AppointmentAgent->>AppointmentAgent: journeyType = CREATE

      alt entryPath missing
        AppointmentAgent-->>User: Clarify service request vs product consultation
        User->>AppointmentAgent: "Product consultation"
      end
      AppointmentAgent->>AppointmentAgent: Set entryPath

      alt topicCode or serviceCode missing
        AppointmentAgent-->>User: Ask for the advisory topic or service reason
        User->>AppointmentAgent: "Mortgage consultation"
      end
      AppointmentAgent->>AppointmentAgent: Set topicCode or serviceCode

      alt consultationChannel missing
        AppointmentAgent-->>User: Ask for branch, video, or phone consultation
        User->>AppointmentAgent: "Branch"
      end
      AppointmentAgent->>AppointmentAgent: Set consultationChannel

    else existing appointment lifecycle
      AppointmentAgent->>AppointmentAgent: journeyType = GET or RESCHEDULE or CANCEL
      AppointmentAgent-->>User: Confirm whether the caller wants details, reschedule, or cancellation
      User->>AppointmentAgent: Lifecycle action
    end
  end

  Note over RootAgent,AppointmentAgent: Output to downstream flows:<br/>{ journeyType, entryPath, topicCode or serviceCode, consultationChannel }
